UPDATE public.onboarding_pages
SET blocks = '[{"type": "callout", "label": "For your coordinator", "text": "Before your new hire''s first day, confirm: laptop is ready, accounts are provisioned (Adobe CC, Figma, Slack, Asana, Google Drive), and their first-week meetings are scheduled."}, {"type": "card", "title": "About Passion City Church", "body": "Passion City Church is a multi-site church based in Atlanta, GA with locations at 515 (main campus), Cumberland, Trilith, and Washington DC. The design team serves every ministry across these campuses — from Sunday services to conferences, students, kids, young adults, and more. Our work is seen weekly by thousands of people in person and online.\n\nOur global ministry, Passion Conferences (268 Generation), reaches college students worldwide. The design team also supports sixstepsrecords, which includes artists like Crowder and Kristian Stanfill."}, {"type": "card", "title": "We Design Everything", "body": "Because God is the most beautiful One of all, beauty matters in all we do. Every sign, place, communication, decoration—every inch of our space is designed.\n\nIntentionally. Culturally. Purposefully.\n\nWe do not believe our design needs to be ostentatious. But we do believe everything needs to be designed. Our design is one of the ways we speak to the world around us and reflect God''s beauty. And because God is in the details, we design down to the smallest level. We value creativity because it points us back to the Creator of all. Regular, ordinary, and usual are not on our list of values.\n\nDesign affirms that we are current and helps us usher His unchanging message to a rapidly evolving world. That''s why we put so much thought and energy into the spaces we invite people into. Before most people hear us, they see us. We want what they see to be inviting, interesting, inspiring, excellent, and compelling.\n\nEveryone isn''t naturally a designer. So if this is not your strong suit, our design team and others are always happy to help.\n\nBecause order communicates purpose, and attention to detail reflects beauty, we pay attention to our surroundings. We displace clutter, wipe counters, straighten pillows, pick up paper towels that miss the trash can, create welcoming spaces, and leave environments looking better than when we arrived."}, {"type": "two_col", "left": {"title": "Design team culture", "body": "We collaborate over competing. Communicate openly (Move DMs to channels when possible). Ask questions early — it saves time for everyone. Creative decisions are typically led by Josh and Matt, with Sophie coordinating resourcing and workflow."}, "right": {"title": "What we value in our work", "body": "Excellence that serves, not impresses. Our design should make it easier for people to encounter God — clear, beautiful, on-brand. When in doubt, ask: does this serve the message?"}}, {"type": "card", "title": "Your role at a glance", "body": "Depending on your track, you''ll be touching different parts of the workflow. Here''s a quick orientation:\n\nJunior (internal transfer) — You know the org. Now you''re learning our design systems, file structures, and creative workflows. Shadow Josh frequently in your first 2 weeks. Don''t hesitate to ask; no question is too small.\n\nMid-level (external hire) — You bring strong design skills. Your first 30 days are about learning context: our brand, our platforms, our teams, and how creative decisions get made here. Resist the urge to change things before you understand why they exist."}]'::jsonb
WHERE slug = 'welcome';